Question: What type of cultural arts or entertainment opportunities would you like to see more of in Austin?

Response ID: resp_3830
Response Text: I would love to see more professional dance (not only ballet, but also modern dance, contemporary dance, cutting-edge and up-and-coming dance). It's a pity that in a city as big as Austin there is only one big Dance organization (Ballet Austin). We need more and more varied dance! 

I also would love to see more opportunities for Drag artists outside of bars. 

I would also love to see cirque arts take off in our city. There are many amazing circuses and I can't remember the last time I heard of a circus coming to Austin. 

Lastly, choral music needs affordable spaces to perform and rehearse in! Churches have been amazing in letting us use their spaces for a fraction of the cost, but for an art that generates community and connection for people of very diverse background, there should be more support from the city. Especially when so many people from marginalized populations do not feel at home in a church.

